deals.highlightsHtml: Tour the famous pyramids of Giza before exploring Cairo on your own during this 7-day vacation in Egypt
deals.pitchHtml:
Gate 1 Travel: 114,000+ of our travelers served since 2012

See Egypt’s Famous Pyramids and Sphinx

Flights & Transportation:

  • Round-trip airfare from New York City (specific gateway based on availability)
  • All transfers
  • Airline taxes & fuel surcharges
  • For additional departure airports/pricing, contact Gate 1 Travel at (800) 682-3333.
  • Airline & flight times determined at time of booking

Hotels (5 nights + 1 overnight flight)

  • 5 nights of accommodations at The Oasis Hotel or similar in Cairo
  • Hotel upgrade available at the time of voucher redemption with Gate 1 Travel
  • Hotel porterage
  • Hotel taxes, fees, and service charges

Attractions & Meals

  • Daily breakfast
  • Morning tour of the pyramids of Giza that includes a visit to the Sphinx that guards the Giza plateau

Ideas for Your Vacation

Built with an estimated 2.3 million limestone blocks totaling more than 6.5 million tons, the massive pyramids of Giza have withstood the sands of time. They’re among the oldest tourist attractions on the planet and the only remaining of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World. During this 7-day vacation from Gate 1 Travel, you’ll get a guided tour of these pyramids, then have the rest of the trip to explore Cairo on your own or go on optional excursions.

  • Khan El-Khalili bazaar: Feel like you’ve been transported to 14th-century Egypt via a labyrinth of brass lanterns and colorful mounds of spices.
  • The Museum of Egyptian Antiquities: Admire its collection of carved sarcophagi and golden jewelry.
  • Al Azhar Park: Stroll along palm-lined paths and enjoy views of Cairo from one of the park’s cafés.

Call Gate 1 Travel at (800) 682-3333 for Questions About:

  • Flying from any airport not listed here
  • Extending your trip or traveling on dates not listed here
  • The availability of your desired travel dates
  • Traveling with kids; children 11 and under do not require a voucher
  • Booking optional tours and upgrades

Optional Tours & Upgrades

  • Hotel upgrade available at the time of voucher redemption with Gate 1 Travel
  • Half-day tour of Memphis and the Saqqara pyramids with lunch on day 3 ($39/person)
  • Dinner cruise on the Nile on day 3 ($75/person)
  • Egyptian Museum with lunch ($49 or $59/person), Coptic Cairo with dinner ($69 or $79/person), or both ($99/person) on day 4
  • Full-day tour of Luxor with round-trip flight and lunch on day 5 ($369/person); Luxor optional tour is not available locally
  • Full-day tour of Alexandria with lunch on day 6 ($99/person)

deals.highlightsHtml: Up to six guests enjoy daily passes to a huge indoor water park, plus access to kid-friendly activities and seven restaurants
deals.pitchHtml:
About Your Great Wolf Lodge Getaway

Travel Dates

  • Book to stay between July 26 and September 14.
  • Prices vary by day; the price listed is the lowest possible and may not be available all days.
  • Click on a date on the booking calendar to see the individual prices by day.

Inclusions

  • Daily water park passes for each registered guest, up to the maximum room occupancy, are included in all options.

See additional details regarding room occupancy, water park passes, and more on the Fine Print & Details tab above. See FAQs here.

Property at a Glance: Great Wolf Lodge Anaheim

The heart and soul of Great Wolf Lodge Anaheim is its 105,000-square-foot indoor water park. Splashy rides such as the Howlin’ Tornado—an enclosed water slide that shoots you through a six-story funnel—and a zero-depth-entry wave pool with 3-foot swells surround the park’s iconic hub: a four-story treehouse with a 1,000-gallon tipping bucket. Younger kids will have a blast with the water slides and gentle spray features of Whooping Hollow and Cub Paw Pool.

The water park, which hovers around 84 degrees all year long, isn’t the resort’s only family-friendly activity. You’ll also find an arcade with more than 100 games and Scooops Kid Spa, complete with ice-cream-sundae pedicure chairs.

  • Extended and exclusive water park access: You can enter the water park at 1 p.m. on the day you check in and stay until close on the day you check out (essentially 2 days’ water park admission). And since there are no day passes for outside visitors, resort guests have exclusive access and won’t get stuck in long lines.
  • Family-friendly fun: There are plenty of games and activities for kids of all ages. Explore all activities by age group here.
  • Hands-on crafts and activities such as face painting and balloon twisting during the Lunch Time Lineup can entertain young children when they want a break from the water park action.
  • Roomy suites comfortably sleep up to six people. Some suites provide extra privacy with enclosed bunk beds.
  • Where to eat: There are seven restaurants and snack bars, including the classy Lodge Wood Fired Grill.
  • Add a Paw Pass or Pup Pass to your stay to enjoy kid-friendly activities and sweets at Creation Station, MagiQuest, Bear Paw Sweets & Eats, and more at a discounted rate. See everything that’s included—as well as other available packages—here (additional fees apply).
  • Safety first: Complimentary life jackets in multiple sizes and trained lifeguards help keep families safe and secure.
  • Distance from Los Angeles and San Diego: 32 miles from Los Angeles and 94 miles from San Diego

All-Inclusive Package

  • In-room minibar with soft drinks, water, and beer (restocked daily)

Grand Bahia Principe Tulum

The 4.5-star Grand Bahia Principe Tulum is nestled next to one of Mexico’s most popular attractions: a white-sand beach. Enjoy a drink from the beach bar in the shade of a gazebo, or hit the waves with snorkeling and kayaking. Head back onshore to indulge in Brazilian and Mexican foods at the resort’s all-inclusive restaurants.

deals.pitchHtml:
Hotel at a Glance: The Explorean Cozumel

Set between the jungle and the Caribbean Sea, The Explorean Cozumel is designed for travelers who want to experience what the island’s landscape has to offer. The 4-star hotel’s all-inclusive package comes with daily adventures ranging from paddleboarding and snorkeling in a coral reef to riding dune buggies to remote beaches. Even the guest rooms encourage visitors to immerse themselves in the environment—there are no TVs, and private balconies look out to the jungle.

  • All-inclusive package: Meals and drinks are covered, along with access to the adjacent Fiesta Americana resort.
  • Locally sourced food and top-shelf drinks help guests unwind.
  • Casitas are set in two-story bungalows with rainfall showerheads and sleek wood furnishings.
  • Recent praise: It was ranked 1 of Mexico’s top 20 hotels in TripAdvisor’s 2018 Travelers’ Choice awards.
  • What’s nearby: About a mile away, Chankanaab Beach Adventure Park has ziplines and dolphin encounters.

Cozumel, Mexico: Relaxed Tropical Island with World-Class Diving

Cozumel, Mexico’s largest Caribbean island, lies just off the eastern coast of the Yucatán peninsula. Compared to Cancún—Mexico’s spring-break capital, located 50 miles north—Cozumel is decidedly laid-back. Formerly a fishing settlement, the island remains blissfully free of high-rise resorts and other signs of overdevelopment. Visitors here tend to focus more on exploring the wilderness than on late-night beach parties. Adventure-tour companies arrange expeditions by land or by sea, including trips to ancient Mayan ruins and the island’s jungles, marshes, and dive sites known for deep canyons and tunnels.

There’s only one city on the island—San Miguel de Cozumel, where street vendors on a waterfront promenade sell everything from jewelry to Cuban cigars. It’s also where you’ll find an assortment of clubs and bars showcasing live reggae-salsa fusion and jazz bands.

Frequently Asked Questions

1. What is the best way to travel to the hotel from the airport? Cozumel International Airport (CZM) is approximately 7 miles away from the resort.

2. Is there an additional occupancy fee, or do I have to make another purchase? The deal covers a stay for two. Adding occupants above standard, please contact the property for details and pricing.

3. Will I be approached to attend a timeshare sales presentation? Customers are never obligated to attend a sales presentation. If you are approached and decline a presentation, you will not lose the value of your voucher or have to pay additional fees.

4. Which activities and amenities are included in the resort credits? Resort credit is not included with the voucher.

5. Are dinner reservations required for restaurants? Is there a dress code? For information regarding your dining options, please click here or call 800-343-7821.

deals.highlightsHtml: Explore national parks, zipline across the rainforest canopy, and relax in hot springs on this 6-day Costa Rica tour; airfare not included
deals.pitchHtml:
Explore Rainforests and Beaches in Costa Rica

Costa Rica’s diverse landscape and animal life make it an ideal destination for eco-tourism. You’ll see plenty of both on this vacation, which includes rainforest tours and visits to hot springs. On the last 2 days, you’ll get a chance to re-energize at a resort near the beach. A full itinerary is available here.

Days 1–3: La Fortuna

After your flight from the United States (airfare not included with this deal), you’ll arrive at Casa Luna Hotel & Spa, a rustic, colonial-style hotel near Arenal Volcano. Day 2 is filled with adventurous activities; day 3 is yours to spend as you choose.

  • Zipline tour: You’ll whiz past colorful birds, over waterfalls, and through lush forests.
  • Arenal Volcano National Park: Keep your eyes peeled for parrots and howler monkeys as you hike through the rainforest.
  • Arenal hot springs: Soothe tired muscles in warm pools created by the volcano’s geothermic activity.

Days 4–6: Jacó Beach

On day 4, you’ll be transported to either the 4-star Oceano Boutique Hotel & Gallery (classic options) or the Best Western Jacó Beach All-Inclusive Resort (all-inclusive options) for a few days of R & R near the Pacific Ocean.

  • Free time: Spend the day exploring the beautiful area surrounding the surfing town with variety of activities like sport fishing tours, surf lessons, ATV’S, nightlife and more.

Frequently Asked Questions

1. What is the best way to travel to the hotel from the airport? Juan Santamaría International Airport (SJO). Ecoterra guides will meet you at the airport to take you to the hotel.

2. Is there an additional occupancy fee, or do I have to purchase another voucher? The voucher covers two guests. Adding occupants above standard is $499 per stay for a guest 12 or older and $399 per stay for each kid aged 5–11 for the classic options and $399 per stay for a guest 12 or older and $299 per stay for each kid aged 5–11 for the all-inclusive options.

3. Will I be approached to attend a timeshare sales presentation? Customers are never obligated to attend a sales presentation. If you are approached and decline a presentation, you will not lose the value of your voucher have to pay additional fees.

4. Which activities and amenities are included in the resort credits? Resort credits are not included with the voucher.

5. Are dinner reservations required for restaurants? Is there a dress code? For information regarding your dining options, please click here or call (800) 332-6498.

Discover the City of Light

Flights & Transportation:

  • Round-trip airfare from New York City (specific gateway based on availability)

Once you arrive in Paris, you’ll get to explore the city at your own pace. You can choose one of the optional tours or roam the city on your own to see iconic sights like the Eiffel Tower, Champs-Élysées, and Arc de Triomphe.
